article.description: Boston University takes care of Navy 55-32
article.headline: Boston University takes care of Navy 55-32
article.linkText: Boston University takes care of Navy 55-32
article.story: BOSTON -- Maurice Watson Jr. scored 11 points, had six assists and six rebounds to lead Boston University past Navy 55-32 on Tuesday. BU held Navy to its lowest point total since a 33-21 loss to Penn State on Feb. 6, 1943. Watson entered the game tied for third nationally with 103 assists for BU (10-6, 3-0 Patriot). Cedric Hankerson had 11 off the bench and Nathan Dieudonne added 10 for the Terriers. Watson was 4 of 11 from the field and BU shot just 38.5 percent. BU held a 25-13 advantage at halftime and went on an 8-0 run to start the second half to take a 20-point lead. Navy only scored six points through the first 10 minutes of the second half and trailed 37-19 after Malik Thomas' basket with 9:55 remaining. Navy (6-8, 1-2) is 5-0 at home this season but fell to 1-8 on the road.
